From ef5ed0f00359d56e7ee1e48a426b63eefacc3c35 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ahmed Wafdy <ahmedadelwafdy782@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 1 Mar 2026 00:49:28 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Clear only ERR_STATUS.V from Xen, never touch ERR_ADDR, so
 ATF's poison signature check can succeed

Implement SDEI Client in Xen

Initialize an early boot SDEI handler at EL2 to accept events from EL3
Firmware.
Ensure the SDEI handler runs with interrupts masked or priority
elevated.

Without this handler, EL3 has no destination for RAS events, causing system asserts

Xen must virtualize SDEI for Guest OSes at EL1.

- Prevent MCE from asserting by pre-clearing the CCPMU ERR0STATUS before MCE checks it
